meta-env
========

`meta-env` codifies the DES Raspberry Pi runtime environment.  It complements
the application and PiRacer layers by providing the baseline image recipe,
boot-time hardware configuration, and system policies that every build should
inherit.

Key components
--------------

* ``recipes-core/images/des-image.bb`` – Reference image that pulls in the
  HeadUnit, Instrument Cluster, and PiRacer controller packages.
* ``recipes-bsp/bootfiles/rpi-config_%.bbappend`` – Enables SPI/I²C and applies
  the MCP2515 CAN overlays in ``config.txt`` so SocketCAN devices are ready at
  boot.
* ``recipes-core/dbus/des-gear-dbus-config.bb`` – Drops the D-Bus policy file
  allowing the gear service to be accessed by the instrument cluster.
* ``recipes-connectivity/connman/connman_%.bbappend`` – Autoconnect tweaks for
  Wi-Fi via ConnMan.
* ``recipes-kernel/modules/i2c-dev-autoload.bb`` – Ensures ``i2c-dev`` is
  autoloaded for the user-space vehicle libraries.

Using the layer
---------------

Add the layer alongside the other meta-custom layers:

.. code-block:: bash

   bitbake-layers add-layer meta-custom/meta-env

Adjust or extend the supplied recipes in your own ``.bbappend`` files if the
vehicle configuration diverges (for example different CAN oscillator values or
custom image package sets).
